  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Frozen Verbs (الأفعال الجامدة)",
      "titleArabic": "الأفعال الجامدة",
      "content": [
        "Frozen verbs (الأفعال الجامدة) are verbs that don't fully conjugate for tense, person, or mood.",
        "They remain in a fixed form and are used for specific grammatical functions."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Don't change for all persons/tenses like regular verbs",
        "Used for specific meanings: negation, hope, praise/blame",
        "Some have limited conjugation (e.g., لَيْسَ)",
        "Others are completely invariable (e.g., نِعْمَ، بِئْسَ)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "لَيْسَ", "english": "is not (negation of existence)" },
        { "arabic": "عَسَى", "english": "perhaps / maybe (hope)" },
        { "arabic": "هَبْ", "english": "suppose / assume" },
        { "arabic": "تَعَالَ", "english": "come! (imperative only)" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Types of Frozen Verbs",
      "titleArabic": "أنواع الأفعال الجامدة",
      "content": [
        "Frozen verbs can be categorized by their function and the extent of their conjugation limitations.",
        "Understanding these verbs is essential for advanced Arabic comprehension."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "لَيْسَ - conjugates for person but not tense (لَسْتُ، لَسْنَا، لَيْسُوا)",
        "عَسَى - limited conjugation, expresses hope (عَسَى أَنْ يَأْتِيَ)",
        "نِعْمَ/بِئْسَ - completely frozen for praise/blame",
        "هَلُمَّ - frozen imperative meaning 'come here'"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "لَسْتُ طَالِبًا", "english": "I am not a student" },
        { "arabic": "عَسَى أَنْ يَنْجَحَ", "english": "Perhaps he will succeed" },
        { "arabic": "هَلُمَّ إِلَيَّ", "english": "Come to me!" },
        { "arabic": "هَاتِ الْكِتَابَ", "english": "Give me the book!" }
      ]
    }
  ],
